Detailed Description

template<typename T>
class roboptim::retargeting::ForwardGeometryChoreonoid< T >

Compute forward geometry for a particular robot model.

Robot model from choreonoid should be passed to the constructor and use for computation. The analytical jacobian must also be retrieved and returned in the impl_gradient/impl_jacobian methods.

Gradient computation.

The jacobian is as follow:

------------------------------------------------------------------ | function id || tx | ty | tz | rx | ry | rz | dof0 | ... | dofN | ------------------------------------------------------------------ | 0 (tx) || 1 | 0 | 0 | | | | 1 (ty) || 0 | 1 | 0 | [1] | Choreonoid | | 2 (tz) || 0 | 0 | 1 | | | | 3 (rx) || 0 | 0 | 0 | | | | 4 (ry) || 0 | 0 | 0 | [2] | Choreonoid | | 5 (rz) || 0 | 0 | 0 | | | ------------------------------------------------------------------

I.e. influence of configuration change on the body position.

In our case, we only compute one line of this array.

Formula [1] and [2] are available in "On the Dynamics Modeling of Free-Floating-Base Articulated Mechanisms and Applications to Humanoid Whole-Body Dynamics and Control", K. Bouyarmane, A. Kheddar.

Parameters:
gradientGradient
xconfiguration (free floating then DOF values)
functionIdjacobian line to be computed
